popt4jlib.neural.costfunction

Class CategoricalAccuracy

  • java.lang.Object
    • popt4jlib.neural.costfunction.CategoricalAccuracy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, FunctionIntf, FFNNCostFunctionIntf

    public class CategoricalAccuracy
extends java.lang.Object
implements FFNNCostFunctionIntf
    measures the accuracy of classification where as error in a vector component counts any quantity that is (not NaN and) larger than 1/2 in absolute value. Notice that the 1/2 value threshold comes from the fact that when deciding the label that corresponds to the output of the network (in categorical classification), the output is simply rounded to the nearest integer (for example an output of 4.32 becomes rounded to 4.0; if the true label is 4, the error is 0.32, else it's always (in absolute value) greater than 1/2.) Since we are always solving a minimization problem, we actually return 100 - accuracy.
